    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and<strong> cornflour </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, with your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!) and <strong>crème fraîche</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted</strong> <strong>spinach</strong> under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>running</strong> <strong>water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
